---
import { PROBLEMS, PLATFORMS, INDUSTRIES, LOCATIONS } from "../data/pseo";
import { siteUrl, breadcrumb, organizationSchema } from "../lib/seo";

// Generate schemas
const breadcrumbSchema = breadcrumb([
  { name: "Home", item: "/" },
  { name: "About SEO Engine" }
]);
const orgSchema = organizationSchema();
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <title>How Our SEO Automation Engine Works | Why Is My Website Slow</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Discover how our advanced SEO automation engine generates hundreds of unique, SEO-optimized pages for different website performance issues, platforms, and industries." />
  <link rel="canonical" href={siteUrl("/about-seo-engine/")} />
  
  <!-- Schema markup -->
  <script type="application/ld+json">{JSON.stringify(breadcrumbSchema)}</script>
  <script type="application/ld+json">{JSON.stringify(orgSchema)}</script>
  
  <!-- Open Graph / Social Media Tags -->
  <meta property="og:title" content="How Our SEO Automation Engine Works | Why Is My Website Slow" />
  <meta property="og:description" content="Discover how our advanced SEO automation engine generates hundreds of unique, SEO-optimized pages for different website performance issues, platforms, and industries." />
  <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
  <meta property="og:url" content={siteUrl("/about-seo-engine/")} />
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/BreadcrumbList">
        <li itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ListItem">
          <a href="/" itemprop="item"><span itemprop="name">Home</span></a>
          <meta itemprop="position" content="1" />
        </li>
        <li itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ListItem">
          <span itemprop="name">About SEO Engine</span>
          <meta itemprop="position" content="2" />
        </li>
      </ol>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main>
    <article>
      <header>
        <h1>How Our SEO Automation Engine Works</h1>
        <p>Discover how we generate hundreds of unique, SEO-optimized pages for different website performance issues, platforms, and industries.</p>
      </header>

      <section>
        <h2>How It Works with WhyIsMyWebsiteSlow.com</h2>
        <p>Our SEO automation engine creates targeted landing pages for specific website performance issues on your domain <strong>whyismywebsiteslow.com</strong>. Rather than using subdomains, all pages are created as subdirectories under your main domain for maximum SEO value.</p>
        
        <h3>URL Structure</h3>
        <p>All generated pages follow a logical URL structure under your main domain:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Problem Pages:</strong> <code>https://whyismywebsiteslow.com/why-is-my-website-slow/[specific-issue]/</code></li>
          <li><strong>Platform Pages:</strong> <code>https://whyismywebsiteslow.com/website-speed-audit/platform/[platform]/</code></li>
          <li><strong>Industry Pages:</strong> <code>https://whyismywebsiteslow.com/website-speed-audit/industry/[industry]/</code></li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>This approach consolidates SEO authority under your primary domain rather than spreading it across subdomains.</p>
        
        <div class="feature-grid">
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Data-Driven Approach</h3>
            <p>All content is generated from structured data in <code>src/data/pseo.ts</code>. Each entry contains detailed information about problems, solutions, statistics, and more.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Template-Based Generation</h3>
            <p>Using Astro's static path generation, we create unique pages from templates that incorporate the data to produce SEO-optimized content.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>SEO Optimization</h3>
            <p>Every generated page includes proper title tags, meta descriptions, schema markup, and keyword optimization.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Types of Pages Generated</h2>
        <p>Our system creates three main types of pages based on different data sets:</p>
        
        <h3>Problem-Specific Pages</h3>
        <p>Targeted pages for specific performance issues like:</p>
        <ul>
          {PROBLEMS.slice(0, 3).map(problem => (
            <li><a href={`/why-is-my-website-slow/${problem.slug}`}>{problem.keyword}</a> → <code>https://whyismywebsiteslow.com/why-is-my-website-slow/{problem.slug}/</code></li>
          ))}
          <li>... and more specific issues</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Platform-Specific Pages</h3>
        <p>Pages tailored to specific website platforms and technologies:</p>
        <ul>
          {PLATFORMS.slice(0, 5).map(platform => (
            <li><a href={`/website-speed-audit/platform/${platform.platform}`}>{platform.keyword}</a> → <code>https://whyismywebsiteslow.com/website-speed-audit/platform/{platform.platform}/</code></li>
          ))}
          <li>... and more platforms</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Industry-Specific Pages</h3>
        <p>Pages focused on performance challenges in specific industries:</p>
        <ul>
          {INDUSTRIES.slice(0, 5).map(industry => (
            <li><a href={`/website-speed-audit/industry/${industry.industry}`}>{industry.keyword}</a> → <code>https://whyismywebsiteslow.com/website-speed-audit/industry/{industry.industry}/</code></li>
          ))}
          <li>... and more industries</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>SEO Features Included</h2>
        <p>Every page generated by our system includes advanced SEO features:</p>
        
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Schema Markup:</strong> FAQ, Breadcrumb, Article, and Organization schemas for rich snippets</li>
          <li><strong>Keyword Optimization:</strong> Proper density and placement for target keywords</li>
          <li><strong>Internal Linking:</strong> Strategic connections between related topics</li>
          <li><strong>Social Media Tags:</strong> Open Graph and Twitter Card tags for sharing</li>
          <li><strong>Canonical URLs:</strong> Prevents duplicate content issues</li>
          <li><strong>Structured Content:</strong> Proper headings, lists, and readable formatting</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Scaling to 200+ Pages</h2>
        <p>Our system is designed to scale effortlessly:</p>
        
        <h3>Current Potential</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Problem Pages:</strong> {PROBLEMS.length} current + potential for 50+ more</li>
          <li><strong>Platform Pages:</strong> {PLATFORMS.length} platform-specific pages</li>
          <li><strong>Industry Pages:</strong> {INDUSTRIES.length} industry-specific pages</li>
          <li><strong>Location Pages:</strong> {LOCATIONS.length} location-specific pages</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>Total Potential:</strong> Over 80+ pages with current data, expandable to 200+ pages</p>
        
        <h3>How to Add More Content</h3>
        <p>To generate more pages, simply add entries to the arrays in <code>src/data/pseo.ts</code>:</p>
        <pre><code>// Example problem entry
&#123;
  slug: "why-is-my-[platform]-site-slow-due-to-[specific-issue]",
  keyword: "why is my [platform] site slow due to [specific issue]",
  h1: "Why Is My [Platform] Site Slow Due to [Specific Issue]?",
  metaDescription: "[Detailed description]",
  platform: "[platform]",
  industry: "[industry]",
  // ... rest of the detailed structure
&#125;</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Real-World Example</h2>
        <p>Here's an example of how a generated page might look for a specific issue:</p>
        
        <div class="example-page">
          <h3>Sample Page Structure</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Title:</strong> Why Is My WordPress Site Slow? Top Causes & Solutions</li>
            <li><strong>Meta Description:</strong> Discover why your WordPress site is slow and learn proven solutions to speed it up...</li>
            <li><strong>H1:</strong> Why Is My WordPress Site Slow? Top Causes & Solutions</li>
            <li><strong>Primary Cause Section:</strong> Detailed explanation of the main issue</li>
            <li><strong>Quick Wins Section:</strong> Actionable steps to improve performance</li>
            <li><strong>Solutions Section:</strong> Detailed, step-by-step fixes</li>
            <li><strong>Statistics Section:</strong> Data-backed impact information</li>
            <li><strong>FAQ Section:</strong> Common questions with answers</li>
            <li><strong>External Resources:</strong> Links to authoritative sources</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Benefits of This Approach</h2>
        <div class="benefits-grid">
          <div class="benefit-card">
            <h3>Efficiency</h3>
            <p>Create hundreds of pages without manual effort, maintaining consistent quality across all content.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="benefit-card">
            <h3>SEO Value</h3>
            <p>Target long-tail keywords and specific user intents that would be difficult to address with generic content.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="benefit-card">
            <h3>Scalability</h3>
            <p>Easily expand to cover new topics, platforms, or industries by adding data entries.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="benefit-card">
            <h3>Consistency</h3>
            <p>Maintain consistent branding, messaging, and SEO practices across all generated pages.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>

    <aside>
      <h2>Ready to Optimize Your Site?</h2>
      <p>Our SEO automation engine powers hundreds of targeted landing pages, but every website has unique performance challenges.</p>
      <a href="/website-speed-audit/" class="cta-button">Get Your Free Website Speed Audit</a>
    </aside>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <p>SEO Automation Engine | Why Is My Website Slow | Generating targeted, valuable content at scale</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
